         <div type="translation">
            <ab>O. MedinHabuGreek 1269, recto: (1) [In your stre]n[gth the king rejoices, O Lord,] (2) and in your [help how he exults]  (3) exceedingly!  The [desi]re (4) [of his soul] you have given to him, and the (5) [request] of his lips you do not withhold.  (6) For [you] meet him (7) with rich [blessings.  Selah.]  (8) You set on [hi]s hea[d] (9) a crown of [precious] stone.  (10) He asked you for life a[nd (11) you gave] to him length (12) of days [forever] and (13) [ever.  Amen.]</ab>
         </div>
